        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A healthy BMI for a child aged 2–12 is any value between the 5th and 85th percentile for their age and sex. For example, a healthy BMI for a 5-year-old boy is approximately 13.6 to 16.8, and for a 10-year-old boy approximately 14.4 to 18.8. These ranges shift at every age, which is why a percentile result is more informative than a raw BMI number." }
